This memorandum, issued by President Barack Obama on August 31, 2009, designates officers of the United States Section, International Boundary and Water Commission, United States and Mexico, to act as the Commissioner of the United States Section in the event that the Commissioner is unable to perform their duties. The designated officers are the United States Section Principal Engineer from the Operations Department and the United States Section Principal Engineer from the Engineering Department. The President retains the discretion to depart from this memorandum in designating an acting Commissioner. The memorandum is intended to improve the internal management of the executive branch and does not create any enforceable rights or benefits. The memorandum is authorized to be published in the Federal Register.